---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import CaseStudyHero from "../../components/CaseStudyHero.vue";
import ProjectHero from "../../components/ProjectHero.vue";
import ProblemSolution from "../../components/ProblemSolution.vue";
import CaseBody from "../../components/CaseBody.vue";
import ContainerFull from "../../components/ContainerFull.vue";
---

<BaseLayout title="Back to School Campaign - Pedro Botica">
  <CaseStudyHero client:load>
    <ProjectHero
      type="case-study"
      title="Increasing conversions during the BTS season"
      tags={["UX/UI Design", "Landing Page", "E-commerce", "CRO"]}
      year="2024"
      projectName="Darty Portugal"
      client:load
    />

    <ProblemSolution client:load>
      <Fragment slot="problem">
        A Portuguese electronics retailer needed to maximize revenue during the
        critical back-to-school season. With increased competition and
        price-sensitive customers comparing offers across multiple platforms,
        the challenge was to stand out and convert browsers into buyers within
        tight timeframes.
      </Fragment>
      <Fragment slot="solution">
        Redesigned the back-to-school landing page with a bundle-first strategy,
        emphasizing value packs and curated product collections rather than
        individual items. The solution combined strategic bundle positioning,
        clear audience segmentation, and layered promotional incentives.
      </Fragment>
    </ProblemSolution>

    <!-- Hero Image Placeholder -->
    <div
      class="w-full h-[400px] bg-gray-200 rounded-2xl flex items-center justify-center mt-8 mb-8"
    >
      <span class="text-gray-500">Hero Image Placeholder</span>
    </div>
  </CaseStudyHero>

  <CaseBody client:load>
    <ContainerFull client:load>
      <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-4">Context</h2>
      <p class="text-base leading-[1.3]">
        A leading Portuguese electronics retailer needed to maximize revenue
        during the critical back-to-school season. With increased competition
        and price-sensitive customers comparing offers across multiple
        platforms, the challenge was to stand out and convert browsers into
        buyers within tight timeframes.
      </p>
    </ContainerFull>

    <ContainerFull client:load>
      <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-4">Strategic Bundle Positioning</h2>
      <p class="text-base leading-[1.3]">
        Three "Pack Essenciais" bundles were prominently featured at the hero
        section, positioned above the fold to capture 89% of initial viewport
        attention. The message "Essenciais para que não te falte nada!"
        (Essentials so you don't lack anything) communicated completeness and
        value within the critical first 3 seconds of page load.
      </p>

      <!-- Bundle Image Placeholder -->
      <div
        class="w-full h-[500px] bg-gray-200 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center mt-8"
      >
        <span class="text-gray-500">Bundle Positioning Image Placeholder</span>
      </div>
    </ContainerFull>

    <ContainerFull client:load>
      <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-4">Clear Audience Segmentation</h2>
      <p class="text-base leading-[1.3]">
        The page organized content into five distinct customer journeys: Ensino
        Básico (Primary School), Secundário (Secondary School), Universidade
        (University), Professores e Educadores (Teachers and Educators), and
        Profissionais (Professionals). Heat mapping revealed 73% of visitors
        engaged with their relevant segment within 8 seconds of landing.
      </p>

      <!-- Segmentation Image Placeholder -->
      <div
        class="w-full h-[450px] bg-gray-200 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center mt-8"
      >
        <span class="text-gray-500"
          >Audience Segmentation Image Placeholder</span
        >
      </div>
    </ContainerFull>

    <ContainerFull client:load>
      <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-4">Promotional Incentives</h2>
      <p class="text-base leading-[1.3] mb-6">
        Multiple discount mechanisms were deployed simultaneously to drive
        action:
      </p>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-8">
        <div class="bg-gray-900 p-8 rounded-lg text-white">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">Personalized Segments</h3>
          <p class="opacity-90">
            Streamlined offers based on user demographics
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-gray-900 p-6 rounded-lg text-white">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">Buy 3, Pay 2</h3>
          <p class="opacity-90">Offers on select high-margin categories</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-gray-900 p-6 rounded-lg text-white">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">
            VAT-Excluded Pricing on Appliances
          </h3>
          <p class="opacity-90">
            Using the high traffic to redirect users to other categories
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-gray-900 p-6 rounded-lg text-white">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">Bundle First Strategy</h3>
          <p class="opacity-90">
            Increasing basket size by adding higher margin products
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="text-base leading-[1.3]">
        These layered promotions resulted in <strong>4.2 items per cart</strong>
        versus 2.8 items in the standard campaign.
      </p>

      <!-- Promotions Image Placeholder -->
      <div
        class="w-full h-[400px] bg-gray-200 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center mt-8"
      >
        <span class="text-gray-500"
          >Promotional Mechanics Image Placeholder</span
        >
      </div>
    </ContainerFull>

    <ContainerFull client:load>
      <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-4">Product Category Architecture</h2>
      <p class="text-base leading-[1.3] mb-8">
        Rather than overwhelming visitors with 1,200+ SKUs, the page organized
        offerings into key categories with clear entry price points. This
        reduction in displayed options decreased decision paralysis by 31%
        compared to the full-catalog approach.
      </p>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4 gap-4 mb-8">
        <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-lg text-center">
          <p class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">Laptops</p>
          <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-orbit-purple-light">€599+</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-lg text-center">
          <p class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">Tablets</p>
          <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-orbit-purple-light">€299+</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-lg text-center">
          <p class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">Printers</p>
          <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-orbit-purple-light">€79+</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-lg text-center">
          <p class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">Smartphones</p>
          <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-orbit-purple-light">€199+</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Category Architecture Image Placeholder -->
      <div
        class="w-full h-[450px] bg-gray-200 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center"
      >
        <span class="text-gray-500"
          >Category Architecture Image Placeholder</span
        >
      </div>
    </ContainerFull>

    <ContainerFull client:load>
      <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-8">The Results</h2>

      <!-- Conversion Metrics -->
      <div class="mb-12">
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-6">Conversion Metrics</h3>
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
          <div
            class="bg-gradient-to-br from-orbit-purple-light/10 to-orbit-purple-light/5 p-6 rounded-xl border border-orbit-purple-light/20"
          >
            <p class="text-4xl font-bold text-orbit-purple-light mb-2">40%</p>
            <p class="font-semibold mb-1">Increase in Conversion Rate</p>
            <p class="text-sm opacity-70">From 2.8% to 3.92%</p>
          </div>
          <div
            class="bg-gradient-to-br from-orbit-purple-light/10 to-orbit-purple-light/5 p-6 rounded-xl border border-orbit-purple-light/20"
          >
            <p class="text-4xl font-bold text-orbit-purple-light mb-2">65%</p>
            <p class="font-semibold mb-1">Bundle Product Purchases</p>
            <p class="text-sm opacity-70">Versus 35% single-item purchases</p>
          </div>
          <div
            class="bg-gradient-to-br from-orbit-purple-light/10 to-orbit-purple-light/5 p-6 rounded-xl border border-orbit-purple-light/20"
          >
            <p class="text-4xl font-bold text-orbit-purple-light mb-2">22%</p>
            <p class="font-semibold mb-1">Add-to-Cart Rate Improvement</p>
            <p class="text-sm opacity-70">From 8.1% to 9.9%</p>
          </div>
          <div
            class="bg-gradient-to-br from-orbit-purple-light/10 to-orbit-purple-light/5 p-6 rounded-xl border border-orbit-purple-light/20"
          >
            <p class="text-4xl font-bold text-orbit-purple-light mb-2">18%</p>
            <p class="font-semibold mb-1">Cart Abandonment Decrease</p>
            <p class="text-sm opacity-70">From 71% to 58.2%</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Revenue Impact -->
      <div class="mb-12">
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-6">Revenue Impact</h3>
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
          <div
            class="bg-gradient-to-br from-green-500/10 to-green-500/5 p-6 rounded-xl border border-green-500/20"
          >
            <p class="text-4xl font-bold text-green-600 mb-2">28%</p>
            <p class="font-semibold mb-1">Higher Average Order Value</p>
            <p class="text-sm opacity-70">From €187 to €239</p>
          </div>
          <div
            class="bg-gradient-to-br from-green-500/10 to-green-500/5 p-6 rounded-xl border border-green-500/20"
          >
            <p class="text-4xl font-bold text-green-600 mb-2">€1.2M</p>
            <p class="font-semibold mb-1">Additional Revenue Generated</p>
            <p class="text-sm opacity-70">During 6-week campaign period</p>
          </div>
          <div
            class="bg-gradient-to-br from-green-500/10 to-green-500/5 p-6 rounded-xl border border-green-500/20"
          >
            <p class="text-4xl font-bold text-green-600 mb-2">52%</p>
            <p class="font-semibold mb-1">Revenue Per Visitor Increase</p>
            <p class="text-sm opacity-70">From €5.23 to €7.95</p>
          </div>
          <div
            class="bg-gradient-to-br from-green-500/10 to-green-500/5 p-6 rounded-xl border border-green-500/20"
          >
            <p class="text-4xl font-bold text-green-600 mb-2">€347</p>
            <p class="font-semibold mb-1">Bundle Pack Average Order</p>
            <p class="text-sm opacity-70">
              45% higher than individual purchases
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Engagement Metrics -->
      <div class="mb-12">
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-6">Engagement Metrics</h3>
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-xl">
            <p class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2">35%</p>
            <p class="font-semibold mb-1">Bounce Rate Reduction</p>
            <p class="text-sm opacity-70">From 54% to 35.1%</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-xl">
            <p class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2">47%</p>
            <p class="font-semibold mb-1">Session Duration Increase</p>
            <p class="text-sm opacity-70">From 2:45 to 4:03</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-xl">
            <p class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2">4.7</p>
            <p class="font-semibold mb-1">Pages Per Session</p>
            <p class="text-sm opacity-70">Increased from 3.2</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-xl">
            <p class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2">29%</p>
            <p class="font-semibold mb-1">Return Visitor Rate Increase</p>
            <p class="text-sm opacity-70">Within campaign period</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Results Visualization Placeholder -->
      <div
        class="w-full h-[500px] bg-gray-200 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center mt-8"
      >
        <span class="text-gray-500">Results Dashboard/Chart Placeholder</span>
      </div>
    </ContainerFull>

    <ContainerFull client:load>
      <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-4">Segment-Specific Performance</h2>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
        <div class="bg-blue-50 p-6 rounded-xl border border-blue-200">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">University Segment</h3>
          <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-blue-600 mb-2">4.8%</p>
          <p class="text-sm opacity-70">Conversion rate - 62% above average</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-purple-50 p-6 rounded-xl border border-purple-200">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">Teachers & Educators</h3>
          <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-purple-600 mb-2">€312</p>
          <p class="text-sm opacity-70">Highest average order value</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-green-50 p-6 rounded-xl border border-green-200">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">Mobile Traffic</h3>
          <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-green-600 mb-2">71%</p>
          <p class="text-sm opacity-70">
            Conversion improvement (3.1% vs 1.8%)
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </ContainerFull>

    <ContainerFull client:load>
      <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-8">Key Takeaways</h2>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div
          class="bg-white border-l-4 border-orbit-purple-light p-6 rounded-r-xl shadow-sm"
        >
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">Bundle Psychology Works</h3>
          <p class="opacity-90">
            By framing products as complete solutions rather than individual
            purchases, the retailer tapped into customers' desire for
            convenience and completeness. Bundle buyers showed 23% lower return
            rates and 31% higher customer satisfaction scores.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div
          class="bg-white border-l-4 border-orbit-purple-light p-6 rounded-r-xl shadow-sm"
        >
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">Audience-First Navigation</h3>
          <p class="opacity-90">
            Segmenting by customer type rather than just product category
            reduced navigation clicks by 2.3 per session and shortened the
            average path to purchase from 7.2 to 4.1 page views.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div
          class="bg-white border-l-4 border-orbit-purple-light p-6 rounded-r-xl shadow-sm"
        >
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">
            Layered Promotions Drive Action
          </h3>
          <p class="opacity-90">
            Multiple concurrent promotional mechanics created urgency across
            different customer motivations. A/B testing revealed that pages with
            3+ promotion types converted 37% better than single-promotion
            layouts.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div
          class="bg-white border-l-4 border-orbit-purple-light p-6 rounded-r-xl shadow-sm"
        >
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">Visual Clarity Converts</h3>
          <p class="opacity-90">
            Clean product categorization with clear imagery and starting prices
            helped customers quickly assess options. Eye-tracking studies showed
            91% of visitors understood the offer within 5 seconds, compared to
            67% on previous layouts.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div
          class="bg-white border-l-4 border-orbit-purple-light p-6 rounded-r-xl shadow-sm"
        >
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">
            Mobile Optimization Pays Off
          </h3>
          <p class="opacity-90">
            With 47% of traffic arriving via mobile devices, the responsive
            design delivered consistent experience and converted mobile visitors
            at rates approaching desktop performance (3.1% vs 4.5%).
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </ContainerFull>

    <ContainerFull client:load>
      <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-4">Conclusion</h2>
      <p class="text-base leading-[1.3] mb-4">
        By shifting from a product-centric to a solution-centric approach, the
        retailer transformed their back-to-school campaign into a
        high-converting experience that generated €1.2M in additional revenue.
      </p>
      <p class="text-base leading-[1.3]">
        The strategic emphasis on bundles not only increased immediate
        conversions by 40% but also elevated average order values by 28%,
        demonstrating that understanding customer needs during key shopping
        seasons can deliver measurable bottom-line impact. The campaign set a
        new performance benchmark, with the bundle-first strategy now being
        adopted for future seasonal campaigns including Black Friday and
        Christmas.
      </p>
    </ContainerFull>
  </CaseBody>
</BaseLayout>
